org.openimaj.util.api.auth

Annotation Type Token


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=TYPE)
@Documented
public @interface Token
    Metadata describing an API token
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      String name
      Get the name of the API with which this token is used
      String url
      Get the URL at which the API parameters can be obtained (usually by the user registering for an account, etc).

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String extraInfo
      Get any additional information about this token or the mechanism by which a user should go about getting the parameters.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        Get the name of the API with which this token is used
        Returns:
        the name of the API with which this token is used

      • url

        public abstract String url
        Get the URL at which the API parameters can be obtained (usually by the user registering for an account, etc).

        the URL at which the API parameters can be obtained.

      • extraInfo

        public abstract String extraInfo
        Get any additional information about this token or the mechanism by which a user should go about getting the parameters. This might displayed to the user by a TokenFactory when querying the user for the Parameters required to access the API.
        Returns:
        additional information about the API and getting the required Parameters.
        Default:
        ""
